article.story: DENTON, Texas -- — Jason Edwards' 37 points led North Texas over Tulane 70-56 on Saturday. Edwards was 10 of 15 shooting, including 8 for 10 from 3-point range, and went 9 for 11 from the line for the Mean Green (9-5, 2-0 American Athletic Conference). C.J. Noland scored 14 points, shooting 4 for 13 (1 for 4 from 3-point range) and 5 of 8 from the free throw line. Aaron Scott scored 10 points and had 12 rebounds. The Green Wave (10-4, 1-1) were led in scoring by Collin Holloway, who finished with 17 points. Tulane also got 10 points and two steals from Sion James. Kevin Cross also had nine points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
